---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Sleep & Perimenopause | The Second Spring"
  description="Waking at 3am, night sweats, light sleep — perimenopause disrupts sleep in specific ways. Here is why it happens and what actually helps."
>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="ig-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-hero-inner">
        <div class="ig-eyebrow">🌙 Topic Guide</div>
        <h1>Sleep & Perimenopause</h1>
        <p>Sleep disruption is one of the most common and most debilitating perimenopausal symptoms. It is hormonal — and it is treatable.</p>
        <div class="ig-share-row">
          <span class="ig-share-label">Share this guide</span>
          <a href="https://wa.me/?text=Why perimenopause disrupts sleep — and what helps — https://thesecondspring.org/guide/sleep" target="_blank" class="ig-share-btn ig-wa">WhatsApp</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 01 — WHY IT HAPPENS -->
  <section class="ig-section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-card-label center">01 / The Hormonal Root</div>
      <h2 class="ig-section-title center">Three hormonal mechanisms that disrupt sleep in perimenopause</h2>

      <div class="steps-grid">
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-number">1</div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Progesterone decline</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">Progesterone has sedative, sleep-promoting properties via GABA-A receptor activity. Its early fall in perimenopause — before oestrogen — makes sleep lighter and more fragmented. This is often the first hormonal sleep change women notice.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-number">2</div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Oestrogen & temperature</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">Falling oestrogen destabilises the hypothalamus's temperature regulation system — producing the night sweats that physically wake you. Even a brief spike in body temperature is enough to break sleep.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step-card">
          <div class="step-number">3</div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3 class="step-title">Cortisol rhythm shift</h3>
            <p class="step-desc">The stress hormone that normally rises gradually at dawn starts rising earlier in perimenopause — causing the characteristic 3–4am waking with a racing mind, heart pounding, and inability to return to sleep.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ig-callout">
        <span class="ig-callout-icon">💡</span>
        <span>Night sweats and insomnia together create a vicious cycle — poor sleep worsens every other perimenopausal symptom including <strong>mood, weight, brain fog, and joint pain</strong>. Addressing sleep is not a luxury — it is foundational.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 02 — PATTERNS OF DISRUPTION -->
  <section class="ig-section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-card-label center">02 / What It Looks Like</div>
      <h2 class="ig-section-title center">The different ways perimenopause disrupts sleep</h2>
      <p class="ig-section-sub center">The most common sleep complaints in women aged 40–55 in India are insomnia and early morning waking. You are not alone — and there are specific reasons this is happening.</p>

      <div class="pattern-grid">
        <div class="pattern-card">
          <div class="pattern-icon">😶</div>
          <h3 class="pattern-title">Difficulty falling asleep</h3>
          <p class="pattern-desc">Racing mind, anxiety, inability to wind down — often driven by elevated cortisol and progesterone deficiency. Your brain loses its natural calming buffer.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-card pattern-card--highlight">
          <div class="pattern-badge">Most characteristic</div>
          <div class="pattern-icon">🕒</div>
          <h3 class="pattern-title">3–4am waking</h3>
          <p class="pattern-desc">The most distinctive perimenopausal sleep pattern — waking in the early hours unable to return to sleep, often with a racing mind or sense of anxiety. Driven by the shifted cortisol rhythm.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-card">
          <div class="pattern-icon">🌡️</div>
          <h3 class="pattern-title">Night sweats</h3>
          <p class="pattern-desc">Hot flashes during sleep that physically wake you, sometimes requiring a change of clothing or sheets. Even when you don't fully wake, they fragment your sleep architecture.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pattern-card">
          <div class="pattern-icon">😴</div>
          <h3 class="pattern-title">Unrefreshing sleep</h3>
          <p class="pattern-desc">Going to bed and waking still exhausted — deep (slow-wave) sleep is directly disrupted by hormonal changes. You may sleep eight hours and feel as if you haven't slept at all.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 03 — WHAT HELPS -->
  <section class="ig-section bg-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-card-label center">03 / What Works</div>
      <h2 class="ig-section-title center">Evidence-based approaches to perimenopausal sleep</h2>
      <p class="ig-section-sub center">Sleep during perimenopause responds best to a combination of addressing the hormonal root cause and supporting good sleep physiology.</p>

      <div class="helps-grid">
        <div class="helps-col">
          <div class="helps-head helps-head--medical">🩺 Medical</div>
          <ul class="helps-list">
            <li><strong>HRT</strong> — addresses the root hormonal cause and is the most effective treatment for perimenopausal sleep disruption overall</li>
            <li><strong>Progesterone specifically</strong> — taken at night for direct sleep benefit via GABA receptor activity</li>
            <li><strong>Gabapentin</strong> — has evidence for sleep improvement in perimenopause</li>
            <li><strong>Treating night sweats directly</strong> — resolving temperature disruption often resolves sleep fragmentation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="helps-col">
          <div class="helps-head helps-head--lifestyle">🌿 Lifestyle</div>
          <ul class="helps-list">
            <li><strong>Bedroom below 20°C</strong> — critical for temperature-disrupted sleep</li>
            <li><strong>No alcohol</strong> — fragments sleep architecture even in small amounts</li>
            <li><strong>No screens 1 hour before bed</strong> — blue light suppresses melatonin</li>
            <li><strong>Consistent wake time</strong> — the single most powerful circadian anchor</li>
            <li><strong>Avoid heavy meals close to bedtime</strong> — digestion raises core body temperature</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="helps-col">
          <div class="helps-head helps-head--support">💊 Supplements with evidence</div>
          <ul class="helps-list">
            <li><strong>Magnesium glycinate 200–400mg</strong> — take before bed; has some evidence for improving sleep quality — avoid if you have kidney disease, and speak to your doctor before starting any supplement</li>
            <li><strong>Melatonin</strong> — helps with sleep onset, less effective for the deeper disruption of night waking</li>
            <li><strong>Ashwagandha</strong> — emerging evidence for cortisol modulation; may help with the 3am cortisol surge</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION 04 — WHEN TO SEEK HELP -->
  <section class="ig-section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-card ig-card--full">
        <div class="ig-card-label">04 / Getting Medical Support</div>
        <h2 class="ig-card-title">When to talk to your doctor about sleep</h2>

        <div class="seek-threshold">
          <div class="seek-icon">📅</div>
          <div class="seek-body">
            <div class="seek-rule">The 4-week rule</div>
            <p>If sleep disruption has lasted more than <strong>4 weeks</strong> and is affecting your daily functioning — concentration, mood, energy, work, relationships — it warrants medical attention. You do not need to wait longer or try harder on your own.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ask-for-grid">
          <div class="ask-for-item">
            <div class="ask-for-label">🧪 Ask for these tests</div>
            <ul class="ask-for-list">
              <li>Hormone levels: FSH, E2 (oestradiol), progesterone</li>
              <li>Thyroid function — hypothyroidism causes insomnia and is common in Indian women</li>
              <li>Ferritin, Vitamin D, B12 — deficiencies worsen sleep quality significantly</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="ask-for-item">
            <div class="ask-for-label">💬 Ask about these treatments</div>
            <ul class="ask-for-list">
              <li>Progesterone therapy — especially taken at night</li>
              <li>Full HRT — if multiple perimenopausal symptoms are present</li>
              <li>Sleep study — if snoring or suspected sleep apnoea, which worsens dramatically in perimenopause</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ig-callout ig-callout--peach">
          <span class="ig-callout-icon">→</span>
          <span>See also: <a href="/guide/symptoms/sleep-problems" class="callout-link">Sleep problems — detailed symptom guide</a> · <a href="/chat" class="callout-link">Talk to The Second Spring companion</a></span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="ig-cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="ig-cta-inner">
        <div class="ig-cta-left">
          <h2>Could poor sleep be hormonal for you?</h2>
          <p>Our free symptom check helps you understand what is happening — and what to ask your gynaecologist. Built specifically for Indian women.</p>
          <div class="ig-cta-btns">
            <a href="/quiz" class="btn btn-peach btn-lg">Check My Symptoms →</a>
            <a href="/chat" class="btn btn-outline-white">Talk Privately</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ig-cta-stat-col">
          <div class="ig-stat"><span class="ig-stat-num">60%</span><span class="ig-stat-label">of perimenopausal women report significant sleep disruption</span></div>
          <div class="ig-stat"><span class="ig-stat-num">3–4am</span><span class="ig-stat-label">the most characteristic perimenopausal waking time</span></div>
          <div class="ig-stat"><span class="ig-stat-num">#1</span><span class="ig-stat-label">sleep complaint in Indian women aged 40–55 is insomnia and early morning waking</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  /* HERO */
  .ig-hero {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0F2A1A 0%, #1A3D2B 60%, #2A5C45 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 6rem 0 5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .ig-hero-inner { max-width: 680px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .ig-eyebrow { display: inline-block; background: rgba(255,255,255,.12); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.2); color: rgba(255,255,255,.85); font-size: .78rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: .1em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: .4rem 1rem; border-radius: 100px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .ig-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.4rem); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -.03em; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .ig-hero p { font-size: 1.1rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,.75); margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .ig-share-row { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .ig-share-label { font-size: .85rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,.55); }
  .ig-share-btn { font-size: .82rem; font-weight: 700; padding: .45rem 1rem; border-radius: 99px; text-decoration: none; }
  .ig-wa { background: #25D366; color: #fff; }

  /* SECTIONS */
  .ig-section { padding: 5rem 0; }
  .bg-white { background: #fff; }
  .bg-cream { background: var(--cream, #F9F5F0); }
  .ig-card-label { font-size: .72rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); background: var(--green-light, #E8F0EB); display: inline-block; padding: .3rem .9rem; border-radius: 99px; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .ig-card-label.center { display: block; text-align: center; }
  .ig-section-title { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -.025em; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); margin-bottom: .75rem; text-align: center; }
  .ig-section-sub { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary, #555); line-height: 1.7; text-align: center; max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto 3rem; }
  .ig-card--full { background: var(--cream, #F9F5F0); border-radius: 20px; padding: 2.5rem; }
  .ig-card-title { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.5vw, 2rem); font-weight: 900; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); letter-spacing: -.02em; margin-bottom: 2rem; }

  /* CALLOUT */
  .ig-callout { display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start; background: var(--green-light, #E8F0EB); border-left: 4px solid var(--green, #1A3D2B); border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0; padding: 1.1rem 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; font-size: .9rem; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); line-height: 1.65; }
  .ig-callout--peach { background: #FEF3EC; border-color: #D4845A; }
  .ig-callout-icon { font-size: 1.3rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .callout-link { color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); font-weight: 700; text-decoration: underline; }

  /* STEPS */
  .steps-grid { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .step-card { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: flex-start; background: var(--cream, #F9F5F0); border-radius: 16px; padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem; border: 1.5px solid var(--border-light, #eee); }
  .step-number { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 900; color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); opacity: .2; line-height: 1; flex-shrink: 0; width: 2.5rem; text-align: center; }
  .step-body { flex: 1; }
  .step-title { font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); margin-bottom: .4rem; }
  .step-desc { font-size: .9rem; color: var(--text-secondary, #555); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }

  /* PATTERNS */
  .pattern-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .pattern-card { background: #fff; border-radius: 16px; padding: 1.5rem; border: 1.5px solid var(--border-light, #eee); position: relative; }
  .pattern-card--highlight { border-color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); border-width: 2px; }
  .pattern-badge { position: absolute; top: -1px; right: 1rem; font-size: .7rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; background: var(--green, #1A3D2B); color: #fff; padding: .25rem .75rem; border-radius: 0 0 8px 8px; }
  .pattern-icon { font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: .75rem; }
  .pattern-title { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); margin-bottom: .4rem; }
  .pattern-desc { font-size: .875rem; color: var(--text-secondary, #555); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }

  /* HELPS */
  .helps-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .helps-col { background: var(--cream, #F9F5F0); border-radius: 16px; padding: 1.5rem; }
  .helps-head { font-size: .9rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-bottom: .75rem; border-bottom: 2px solid; }
  .helps-head--medical { border-color: #D4845A; color: #9D4E1E; }
  .helps-head--lifestyle { border-color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); }
  .helps-head--support { border-color: #7FB89A; color: #2A5C45; }
  .helps-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .6rem; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .helps-list li { font-size: .85rem; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); line-height: 1.55; padding-left: 1rem; position: relative; }
  .helps-list li::before { content: '→'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--green, #1A3D2B); font-size: .75rem; }

  /* SEEK HELP */
  .seek-threshold { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: flex-start; background: #fff; border-radius: 14px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; border: 1.5px solid var(--border-light, #eee); }
  .seek-icon { font-size: 2rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .seek-body { flex: 1; }
  .seek-rule { font-size: .75rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; color: #D4845A; margin-bottom: .4rem; }
  .seek-body p { font-size: .9rem; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
  .ask-for-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .ask-for-item { background: #fff; border-radius: 14px; padding: 1.25rem; border: 1.5px solid var(--border-light, #eee); }
  .ask-for-label { font-size: .82rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text, #1a1a1a); margin-bottom: .75rem; }
  .ask-for-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .45rem; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .ask-for-list li { font-size: .84rem; color: var(--text-secondary, #555); line-height: 1.55; padding-left: 1rem; position: relative; }
  .ask-for-list li::before { content: '·'; position: absolute; left: 0; font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1; color: #D4845A; font-weight: 900; }

  /* CTA */
  .ig-cta-section { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0F2A1A, #1A3D2B); padding: 5rem 0; color: #fff; }
  .ig-cta-inner { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 4rem; align-items: center; }
  .ig-cta-left h2 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -.03em; color: #fff; margin-bottom: .75rem; }
  .ig-cta-left p { font-size: 1rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,.75); margin-bottom: 1.75rem; line-height: 1.65; }
  .ig-cta-btns { display: flex; gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-peach { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; padding: .75rem 1.5rem; background: #D4845A; color: #fff; border-radius: 99px; font-weight: 700; font-size: .9rem; text-decoration: none; transition: all .18s; }
  .btn-peach:hover { background: #bf7249; }
  .btn-lg { padding: .85rem 1.75rem; font-size: 1rem; }
  .btn-outline-white { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; padding: .75rem 1.5rem; border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,.4); color: #fff; border-radius: 99px; font-weight: 700; font-size: .9rem; text-decoration: none; transition: all .18s; }
  .btn-outline-white:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,.1); }
  .ig-cta-stat-col { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
  .ig-stat { background: rgba(255,255,255,.07); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12); border-radius: 14px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .25rem; }
  .ig-stat-num { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 900; color: #FBBF81; letter-spacing: -.03em; }
  .ig-stat-label { font-size: .83rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,.7); line-height: 1.4; }

  /* RESPONSIVE */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .pattern-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .helps-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .ask-for-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .ig-cta-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2.5rem; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .step-card { flex-direction: column; gap: .75rem; }
    .step-number { font-size: 1.5rem; width: auto; }
    .seek-threshold { flex-direction: column; gap: .75rem; }
    .ig-cta-btns { flex-direction: column; }
  }
</style>
